  "body": "# ðŸ’Ž Issue\r\n\r\n### Background\r\n\r\nThe fork choice store type does not store the genesis time of the beacon chain. In some recent changes to the fork choice algorithm, there is a function called `BoostProposerRoot` in #10083 \r\n\r\n```go\r\nfunc (f *ForkChoice) BoostProposerRoot(_ context.Context, blockSlot types.Slot, blockRoot [32]byte, genesisTime time.Time) error\r\n```\r\nwhich requires the genesis time on every call. Instead, the actual `type ForkChoice struct` should track this value.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nThis issue will require some refactoring, as we initialize the fork choice store in `node/node.go` before the rest of the services in Prysm. However, we only receive the genesis time after the `blockchain` service initializes. We might want to move the call to `forkchoice.New()` to within the blockchain service, and we must take to avoid any unintended consequences.\r\n",
